	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hehe....Okay. I play on the Seventh hammer server in the crushbone area(Send tells to Hairfoot), and I notice that so many people play ogres, trolls, and barbarians "because they do a lot of damage". This is a bold face lie. In later levels you will need to group, and the ones dealing the damage will be the fingerwagglers smashing mobs around with (insert ungodly amount here) damage spells a pop for next to no mana for them, and yet you want to do damage? Be a fingerwaggler if so. On to why I play Halfling warriors. The stats. Agility and Dexterity mean better combat skills and being hit less often, making mobs hate you cause they can't hit you while you are smacking them around. So not being hit+hiting often= prime tank material. Tanks are responsible not nessacarly for taking damage, but for keeping the mobs occupied. Of course that is just my opinion and I could be wrong.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
