	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Aug 17th 6:50 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.30]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>There seems to be quite a lot of confusion not only on playing a warrior but also creating one.<br>I will deal first with creating a warrior.<br><br>On creating a warrior you have three main choices.<br>1. Create a warrior to do massive damage.<br>2. Create a warrior to do lots of critical hits<br>3 Create a warrior that Procs alot.<br>Please note that these three choices ingnore the art of roleplaying.<br><br>It is now quite commonly known that Agility is the key ingredient to do critical hits while dexterity will make you proc alot more with proc weapons.<br><br>When i first wanted to start a warrior i looked at all possible races and starting stats.<br><br>I wanted a race that could hit hard and still take alot of punishment however i didnt want to just do the Ogre all str all stamina routine which seems to be far too common.<br>If you ask high level warriors(which i did) what would they change if they could, they all say they would put more into dex. A high dexterity will make you proc alot and with the aid of a high lvl shaman buff you can expect to proc 3 or 4 times a combat.<br>Now i have a friend who plays a dark elf warrior who went all dex and agil. He is a procing machine however due to the low strength the damage dealt when not procing is minimul.<br><br>My choice became clear-<br>I took and Ogre warrior and placed all my points into dexterity and the left over into agility.<br><br>Being an Ogre you have a starting str that cannot be slightly challenged by any other races starting str. Because of this i felt no need to increase this stat as the only characters that i would meet with better starting strength than I would be another Ogre.<br><br>Again my stamina is also so much better than any other race this too i left alone. <br>My dexterity although very poor to start with can be increased to quite a decent level and with a few decent items that you can come across my base dex now sits at 140. With shaman buffs and depending on what weapon i wield this stat hits the high 180.s low 190s. Now i am a procing machine. I dual wield two Yaks and proc atleast 4 times in an average fight. This may not sound alot but its an extra 300 damage if not resisted and while im not procing i am beating them to death with a buffed str of 185.<br><br>All this is to show you that before you start and again not taking into account roleplaying you need to work out what style of warrior you want to play. My choice was a strong healthy warrior that when given the right weapons can proc on a regular basis. <br><br>Now there will be many people who disagree with what i have said but i am not suggesting in any way that one warrior race is better than another. I have merely done my research and i believe taken the most logical steps to creating a high procing damage dealing warrior.<br><br>You must remember that there is no best race class combo to play as all have their benefits.<br><br>I hope this post has given you some insights into the journey of the warrior.<br><br>We are still the finest tanking class in the game and i will be posting more on tactics and guides at a later date.<br><br>Give me strength mighty Rallos Zek to smite thy enemy.<br><br>Molek Ulardisorda (Fennin)<br>&nbsp;<br>Molek Ulardisorda</td></tr>
